{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/healthcare-associated-infections/how-this-topic-was-developed/evidence-exclusion-criteria/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"1ebee9ee-0cf0-5783-be0f-28f61425026c","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 45a41422-cc21-4723-832a-aa0600b96a92 --><h2>Evidence exclusion criteria</h2><!-- end field 45a41422-cc21-4723-832a-aa0600b96a92 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 2d105bb0-3fe6-44fc-803c-aa0600b96a92 --><!-- begin field 14497309-2516-43ef-aba4-aa0600b96a92 --><h2>Our policy</h2><!-- end field 14497309-2516-43ef-aba4-aa0600b96a92 --><!-- begin field d50ccba7-b886-40cd-a392-aa0600b96a92 --><p>Scoping a literature search, and reviewing the evidence for CKS is a methodical and systematic process that is carried out by the lead clinical author for each topic. Relevant evidence is gathered in order that the clinical author can make fully informed decisions and recommendations. It is important to note that some evidence may be excluded for a variety of reasons. These reasons may be applied across all CKS topics or may be specific to a given topic.</p><p>Studies identified during literature searches are reviewed to identify the most appropriate information to author a CKS topic, ensuring any recommendations are based on the best evidence. We use the principles of the GRADE and PICOT approaches to assess the quality of published research. We use the principles of AGREE II to assess the quality of published guidelines.</p><!-- end field d50ccba7-b886-40cd-a392-aa0600b96a92 --><!-- begin field 0e137d92-474c-4d41-9123-aa0600b96a92 --><h2>Standard exclusions for scoping literature:</h2><!-- end field 0e137d92-474c-4d41-9123-aa0600b96a92 --><!-- begin field f32e9a05-1480-4929-b5c7-aa0600b96a92 --><ul><li>Animal studies</li><li>Original research is not written in English</li></ul><!-- end field f32e9a05-1480-4929-b5c7-aa0600b96a92 --><!-- begin field f74b1271-6d77-4108-a970-aa0600b96a92 --><h2>Possible exclusions for reviewed literature:</h2><!-- end field f74b1271-6d77-4108-a970-aa0600b96a92 --><!-- begin field 94c22180-d06e-4c63-8191-aa0600b96a92 --><ul><li>Sample size too small or study underpowered</li><li>Bias evident or promotional literature</li><li>Population not relevant</li><li>Intervention/treatment not relevant</li><li>Outcomes not relevant</li><li>Outcomes have no clear evidence of clinical effectiveness</li><li>Setting not relevant</li><li>Not relevant to UK</li><li>Incorrect study type</li><li>Review article</li><li>Duplicate reference</li></ul><!-- end field 94c22180-d06e-4c63-8191-aa0600b96a92 --><!-- end item 2d105bb0-3fe6-44fc-803c-aa0600b96a92 -->","topic":{"id":"6a4764db-67e6-5a98-ad6f-450c98a82a25","topicId":"97f6f71a-7aa5-40ec-8a1b-aa0600b96730","topicName":"Healthcare-associated infections","slug":"healthcare-associated-infections","lastRevised":"Last revised in MayÂ 2019","chapters":[{"id":"6d22e1d5-d924-5b35-8750-a68b353cf1c4","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"7676fe08-e0bb-533d-aaeb-0b6a165afc02","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"ca5b2485-595e-5e3d-b431-afae6f7ea462","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"13692747-772c-59af-878c-b5bd4e7d8f4b","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"842d291b-7bba-54bb-bdc7-aa98dec75eca","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"22146da3-7bcc-509f-b3df-f619d7b3c4de","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"82adee8f-ee92-5d1f-a594-7e645d87be0d","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"bfa2782f-56ea-519b-bbda-9bff4f111c97","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"9690beb1-f078-50f4-99b9-ee25b041ab50"